     <div class="cont_full"> 
      <div class="cont_half"> 
       <div class="clipper"> 
        <p class="title"><span class="str">&nbsp;</span><span>Geological Heritage of Hong Kong</span><span class="end">&nbsp;</span></p> 
       </div> 
       <div class="explore"> 
        <div class="img_cont"> 
         <img src="/f/frontpage/77/434c146/bookCover_1417488435_1417489461.png" alt="Geological Heritage of Hong Kong"> 
        </div> 
        <!--templateType-white-->
        <!--templateType-half-width-->
        <h6>'Geological Heritage of Hong Kong' by&nbsp;Prof.&nbsp;Chan Lung Sang</h6> 
        <p>We are delighted to announce the publication of <a href="http://www.aristo.com.hk/books/GeologicalHeritage/cover.html"><span style="color:#0000CD;">'Geological Heritage of Hong Kong'</span></a> by Prof. Chan Lung Sang. Prof. Chan's book&nbsp;provides comprehensive coverage of Hong Kong's geological heritage, including many little known localities with interesting geological features. Packed with fascinating pictures of geological localities taken from unusual angles, <span style="font-family: 'Lucida Sans Unicode', 'Lucida Grande', sans-serif, d1n; font-size: 11px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; line-height: 20.3500003814697px;">'Geological Heritage of Hong Kong'</span> is also well-illustrated with annotated explanations of geological features. <span style="font-family: 'Lucida Sans Unicode', 'Lucida Grande', sans-serif, d1n; font-size: 11px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; line-height: 20.3500003814697px;">The book was</span> written for geopark visitors craving for more in-depth understanding of our local geological heritage, and&nbsp;makes valuable comparisons with worldwide examples to place this understanding into a global context. The book promises to be an invaluable resource for people interested&nbsp;in Hong Kong's wonderful geological legacy. Congratulations Prof. Chan!</p> 
       </div> 
      </div> 
